article.description: — Tevian Jones had 22 points as Southern Utah defeated Idaho 75-59 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Jones scores 22 to lead S. Utah over Idaho 75-59
article.linkText: Jones scores 22 to lead S. Utah over Idaho 75-59
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- — Tevian Jones had 22 points as Southern Utah defeated Idaho 75-59 on Thursday night. John Knight III had 14 points for Southern Utah (14-6, 8-2 Big Sky Conference). Maizen Fausett added 12 points and nine rebounds. Dre Marin had 12 points. Mikey Dixon had 17 points for the Vandals (5-17, 2-10). Rashad Smith added 11 points and six rebounds. Trevante Anderson had 11 points. The Thunderbirds, who also defeated Idaho 81-75 on Dec. 4., swept the season series with the Vandals. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
